
# <type>(scope): <subject>
# |<------------------------------------- max 100 characters ------------------------------------->|

# <body>
# |<--------------------------------- max 100 characters per line -------------------------------->|

# <footer>
# |<--------------------------------- max 100 characters per line -------------------------------->|

# Types:
# feat     ✨  A new feature
# fix      🐛  A bug fix
# docs     📚  Documentation only changes
# style    💎  Changes that do not affect the meaning of the code
# refactor 📦  A code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
# perf     🚀  A code change that improves performance
# test     🚨  Adding or correcting tests
# build    🛠  Changes that affect the build system or external dependencies
# ci       ⚙️  Changes to CI configuration files and scripts
# chore    ♻️  Other changes that don't modify src or test files
# revert   🗑  Reverts a previous commit
#
# Scopes (optional):
# cli          Command-line interface and argument parsing
# config       Configuration file parsing and management
# cache        Caching system and cache management
# performance  Mirror performance testing and rating
# lib          Core library functionality (filtering, sorting, validation)
# error        Error handling and error types
# docs         Documentation (README, man pages, CONTRIBUTING, etc.)
# test         Test files and test utilities
# build        Build configuration (Cargo.toml, deny.toml)
# completions  Shell completion files
# packaging    PKGBUILD and distribution packaging
# systemd      Systemd service and timer configurations
# deps         Dependency updates and management

# For the subject:
# - Use imperative, present tense: "change" not "changed" nor "changes"
# - Don't capitalize the first letter
# - No period at the end

# For the body:
# - Explain the motivation for the change and how it differs from previous behavior

# For the footer:
# - BREAKING CHANGE: <description> (for breaking changes)
# - fix #<issue> (to close an issue)
# - re #<issue> (to reference an issue)